{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01N886Cjio4231aX7iGqsgDq","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# mongodb/custom-roles\n2\t# MongoDB custom-roles task\n3\t\n4\tparams:\n5\t  cluster_prefix:\n6\t    default: mongodb-replica\n7\t    description: StatefulSet name of the replica set members.\n8\t  replica_set_name:\n9\t    default: mongodb-replica\n10\t    description: MongoDB replica set _id used when initiating the set.\n11\t  admin_secret_name:\n12\t    default: admin-user-password\n13\t    description: Kubernetes Secret holding the admin user's password.\n14\t  reporting_secret_name:\n15\t    default: reporting-user-password\n16\t    description: Kubernetes Secret holding the reporting user's password.\n17\t  admin_username:\n18\t    default: admin-user\n19\t    description: Username of the MongoDB admin user.\n20\t  reporting_username:\n21\t    default: reporting-user\n22\t    description: Username of the reporting user.\n23\t  app_database:\n24\t    default: appdb\n25\t    description: Application database holding the reporting collections.\n26\t  reports_collection:\n27\t    default: reports\n28\t    description: Collection backing the reporting dashboards.\n29\t  raw_collection:\n30\t    default: raw\n31\t    description: Collection with ingestion data that must not be exposed.\n32\t  bad_role_name:\n33\t    default: rawRead\n34\t    description: Overly-permissive role initially granted to the reporting user.\n35\t\n36\tprompt: |\n37\t  A 3-member MongoDB replica set is running in the mongodb namespace.\n38\t  Authentication is enabled. Passwords are stored in these Secrets:\n39\t  - {{params.admin_secret_name}}\n40\t  - {{params.reporting_secret_name}}\n41\t\n42\t  Reporting dashboards are failing for {{params.reporting_username}} after a permissions change.\n43\t  Dashboards are built from {{params.app_database}}.{{params.reports_collection}}. {{params.app_database}}.{{params.raw_collection}} contains ingestion data and\n44\t  must not be exposed. Restore the minimum access needed for reporting dashboards.\n45\t\n46\t  Notes:\n47\t  - Do not use operators or CRDs.\n48\t\n49\tnamespace_contract:\n50\t  required_roles: []\n51\t\n52\tmetrics:\n53\t  - time_to_first_mutation\n54\t\n55\tpreconditionUnits:\n56\t  - name: mongo_env_ready\n57\t    on_probe_fail: skip\n58\t    probe:\n59\t      # AUTHORITATIVE skip-if-running probe (P32): succeed when the canonical\n60\t      # StatefulSet exists OR any pod is Running, so the destructive namespace\n61\t      # rebuild below is skipped on an inherited cluster even if its pods are\n62\t      # momentarily not Running (mid-restart from a prior stage) -- the\n63\t      # StatefulSet persists across that window. The bare `grep -c Running`\n64\t      # could miss such a cluster and clobber inherited state.\n65\t      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb get statefulset {{params.cluster_prefix}} >/dev/null 2>&1 || kubectl -n mongodb get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -q Running'\"\n66\t        timeout_sec: 10\n67\t    apply:\n68\t      - command: |\n69\t          /bin/sh -c '\n70\t          kubectl delete namespace mongodb --ignore-not-found=true; kubectl wait --for=delete namespace/mongodb --timeout=120s || true\n71\t          '\n72\t        sleep: 2\n73\t      - command: \"kubectl create namespace mongodb\"\n74\t        sleep: 1\n75\t      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/custom-roles/resource/secrets.yaml\"\n76\t        sleep: 1\n77\t      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/custom-roles/resource/services.yaml\"\n78\t        sleep: 1\n79\t      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/custom-roles/resource/statefulset.yaml\"\n80\t        sleep: 5\n81\t      - command: |\n82\t          for i in $(seq 1 120); do\n83\t            ready=$(kubectl -n mongodb get sts {{params.cluster_prefix}} -o jsonpath='{.status.readyReplicas}' 2>/dev/null)\n84\t            if [ \"${ready:-0}\" -ge 3 ]; then\n85\t              exit 0\n86\t            fi\n87\t            sleep 5\n88\t          done\n89\t          exit 1\n90\t        sleep: 2\n91\t      # Pod-Ready != mongod accepting TCP (§1.10): ping-until-ok before rs.initiate.\n92\t      - command: |\n93\t          for i in $(seq 1 30); do\n94\t            kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval 'db.runCommand({ping:1}).ok' 2>/dev/null | grep -q 1 && exit 0\n95\t            sleep 3\n96\t          done\n97\t          exit 1\n98\t        sleep: 2\n99\t      - command: |\n100\t          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval '\n101\t          rs.initiate({_id:\"{{params.replica_set_name}}\",members:[\n102\t            {_id:0,host:\"mongodb-replica-0.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"},\n103\t            {_id:1,host:\"mongodb-replica-1.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"},\n104\t            {_id:2,host:\"mongodb-replica-2.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"}\n105\t          ]})'\n106\t        sleep: 5\n107\t      - command: |\n108\t          for i in $(seq 1 20); do\n109\t            kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval 'db.hello().isWritablePrimary' | grep true && exit 0\n110\t            sleep 3\n111\t          done\n112\t          exit 1\n113\t        sleep: 2\n114\t      - command: |\n115\t          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval '\n116\t          db.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({\n117\t            user: \"{{params.admin_username}}\",\n118\t            pwd: \"admin123password\",\n119\t            roles: [\n120\t              {role: \"clusterAdmin\", db: \"admin\"},\n121\t              {role: \"userAdminAnyDatabase\", db: \"admin\"},\n122\t              {role: \"readWriteAnyDatabase\", db: \"admin\"}\n123\t            ]\n124\t          })'\n125\t        sleep: 2\n126\t      - command: |\n127\t          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet \\\n128\t          \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:admin123password@localhost:27017/admin\" \\\n129\t          --eval 'db.getSiblingDB(\"{{params.app_database}}\").createRole({\n130\t            role: \"{{params.bad_role_name}}\",\n131\t            privileges: [\n132\t              { resource: { db: \"{{params.app_database}}\", collection: \"{{params.raw_collection}}\" }, actions: [\"find\"] }\n133\t            ],\n134\t            roles: []\n135\t          })'\n136\t        sleep: 2\n137\t      - command: |\n138\t          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet \\\n139\t          \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:admin123password@localhost:27017/admin\" \\\n140\t          --eval 'db.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({\n141\t            user: \"{{params.reporting_username}}\",\n142\t            pwd: \"reporting123password\",\n143\t            roles: [{role: \"{{params.bad_role_name}}\", db: \"{{params.app_database}}\"}]\n144\t          })'\n145\t        sleep: 2\n146\t      - command: |\n147\t          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet \\\n148\t          \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:admin123password@localhost:27017/admin\" \\\n149\t          --eval 'db.getSiblingDB(\"{{params.app_database}}\").{{params.reports_collection}}.insertMany([{x:1},{x:2},{x:3}], {writeConcern:{w:1}})'\n150\t        sleep: 2\n151\t      - command: |\n152\t          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet \\\n153\t          \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:admin123password@localhost:27017/admin\" \\\n154\t          --eval 'db.getSiblingDB(\"{{params.app_database}}\").{{params.raw_collection}}.insertMany([{x:10},{x:11}], {writeConcern:{w:1}})'\n155\t        sleep: 2\n156\t    verify:\n157\t      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n158\t        timeout_sec: 10\n159\t\n160\t  - name: admin_user_fixture\n161\t    # Composition self-sufficiency: this case authenticates as the `admin-user`\n162\t    # created at deploy. On an inherited cluster a no-auth/other predecessor may\n163\t    # not have created it, and a live user's password is unrecoverable -> the\n164\t    # oracle's (and the user fixtures') admin auth fails through no agent fault.\n165\t    # Bring our own additively: if admin-user already authenticates, skip; else\n166\t    # ensure the secret and create the user. No restart, no data touched,\n167\t    # idempotent -> never regresses a cluster where admin already works.\n168\t    on_probe_fail: skip\n169\t    probe:\n170\t      - command: |\n171\t          /bin/sh -c '\n172\t          t=\"\"; for cca in /etc/tls/ca.crt /etc/mongo-ca/ca.crt; do kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- ls $cca >/dev/null 2>&1 && { t=\"--tls --tlsAllowInvalidHostnames --tlsAllowInvalidCertificates --tlsCAFile $cca\"; break; }; done\n173\t          pw=$(kubectl -n mongodb get secret admin-user-password -o jsonpath=\"{.data.password}\" 2>/dev/null | base64 -d 2>/dev/null)\n174\t          [ -n \"$pw\" ] || exit 1\n175\t          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet $t \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:$pw@localhost:27017/admin\" --eval \"db.runCommand({ping:1}).ok\" 2>/dev/null | grep -q 1\n176\t          '\n177\t        timeout_sec: 30\n178\t    apply:\n179\t      # Ensure the admin secret (idempotent: create only if missing).\n180\t      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb get secret admin-user-password >/dev/null 2>&1 || kubectl -n mongodb create secret generic admin-user-password --from-literal=password=admin123password'\"\n181\t        sleep: 1\n182\t      # Ensure the admin-user MongoDB user. On a no-auth inherited cluster this\n183\t      # runs unauthenticated and succeeds; where it already exists it errors and\n184\t      # the `|| true` keeps it a no-op. Never drops or alters existing users/data.\n185\t      - command: |\n186\t          /bin/sh -c '\n187\t          t=\"\"; for cca in /etc/tls/ca.crt /etc/mongo-ca/ca.crt; do kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- ls $cca >/dev/null 2>&1 && { t=\"--tls --tlsAllowInvalidHostnames --tlsAllowInvalidCertificates --tlsCAFile $cca\"; break; }; done\n188\t          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet $t --eval \"db.getSiblingDB(\\\"admin\\\").createUser({user:\\\"{{params.admin_username}}\\\",pwd:\\\"admin123password\\\",roles:[{role:\\\"root\\\",db:\\\"admin\\\"}]})\" 2>/dev/null || true\n189\t          '\n190\t        sleep: 2\n191\t    verify:\n192\t      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb get secret admin-user-password >/dev/null 2>&1 && echo ok'\"\n193\t        timeout_sec: 15\n194\t\n195\t  # Additive credential+role+seed fixture (composition safety): standalone the\n196\t  # build above creates the reporting-user, its rawRead role, the\n197\t  # reporting-user-password secret, and the reports/raw seed data. Chained on an\n198\t  # INHERITED cluster that build is skipped, so the oracle fails with\n199\t  # \"reporting-user-password not found\". Ensure each artifact additively when\n200\t  # missing, authenticating as the LIVE admin user (a prior rotation respected)\n201\t  # and writing on the current primary. Never drops/alters existing users/data;\n202\t  # standalone the probe finds everything present and skips -> identical behaviour.\n203\t  - name: reporting_user_fixture\n204\t    on_probe_fail: skip\n205\t    probe:\n206\t      - command: |\n207\t          /bin/sh -c 't=\"\"; for cca in /etc/tls/ca.crt /etc/mongo-ca/ca.crt; do kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- ls $cca >/dev/null 2>&1 && { t=\"--tls --tlsAllowInvalidHostnames --tlsAllowInvalidCertificates --tlsCAFile $cca\"; break; }; done; kubectl -n mongodb get secret {{params.reporting_secret_name}} >/dev/null 2>&1 || exit 1; pw=$(kubectl -n mongodb get secret {{params.admin_secret_name}} -o jsonpath=\"{.data.password}\" 2>/dev/null | base64 -d 2>/dev/null); pw=${pw:-admin123password}; P=\"\"; for _pi in $(seq 1 30); do P=$(kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet $t \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:$pw@localhost:27017/admin?directConnection=true\" --eval '\\''rs.hello().primary'\\'' 2>/dev/null | cut -d. -f1); [ -n \"$P\" ] && break; sleep 2; done; P=${P:-mongodb-replica-0}; kubectl -n mongodb exec \"$P\" -- mongosh --quiet $t \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:$pw@localhost:27017/admin\" --eval '\\''db.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").getUser(\"{{params.reporting_username}}\")?quit(0):quit(1)'\\'' >/dev/null 2>&1'\n208\t        timeout_sec: 30\n209\t    apply:\n210\t      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/custom-roles/resource/secrets.yaml\"\n211\t        sleep: 1\n212\t      - command: |\n213\t          /bin/sh -c 'pw=$(kubectl -n mongodb get secret {{params.admin_secret_name}} -o jsonpath=\"{.data.password}\" 2>/dev/null | base64 -d 2>/dev/null); pw=${pw:-admin123password}; P=\"\"; for _pi in $(seq 1 30); do P=$(kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:$pw@localhost:27017/admin?directConnection=true\" --eval '\\''rs.hello().primary'\\'' 2>/dev/null | cut -d. -f1); [ -n \"$P\" ] && break; sleep 2; done; P=${P:-mongodb-replica-0}; kubectl -n mongodb exec \"$P\" -- mongosh --quiet \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:$pw@localhost:27017/admin\" --eval '\\''var a=db.getSiblingDB(\"{{params.app_database}}\"); if(!a.getRole(\"{{params.bad_role_name}}\")){a.createRole({role:\"{{params.bad_role_name}}\",privileges:[{resource:{db:\"{{params.app_database}}\",collection:\"{{params.raw_collection}}\"},actions:[\"find\"]}],roles:[]});} if(!db.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").getUser(\"{{params.reporting_username}}\")){db.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({user:\"{{params.reporting_username}}\",pwd:\"reporting123password\",roles:[{role:\"{{params.bad_role_name}}\",db:\"{{params.app_database}}\"}]});} if(a.{{params.reports_collection}}.countDocuments({})<3){a.{{params.reports_collection}}.insertMany([{x:1},{x:2},{x:3}],{writeConcern:{w:1}});} if(a.{{params.raw_collection}}.countDocuments({})<2){a.{{params.raw_collection}}.insertMany([{x:10},{x:11}],{writeConcern:{w:1}});}'\\'' 2>&1 || true'\n214\t        sleep: 2\n215\t    verify:\n216\t      - command: |\n217\t          /bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb get secret {{params.reporting_secret_name}} >/dev/null 2>&1; true'\n218\t        timeout_sec: 30\n219\t\n220\toracle:\n221\t  verify:\n222\t    commands:\n223\t      - command: \"python3 cases/mongodb/custom-roles/oracle/oracle.py\"\n224\t        timeout_sec: 150\n225\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"344c96d2-3a99-4ba7-b37e-1a951ea3e6a4","uuid":"c443610d-2110-4fe5-96eb-81f23c2ce91a","timestamp":"2026-07-03T12:42:57.463Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/mydata/karma/cases/mongodb/custom-roles/test.yaml","content":"# mongodb/custom-roles\n# MongoDB custom-roles task\n\nparams:\n  cluster_prefix:\n    default: mongodb-replica\n    description: StatefulSet name of the replica set members.\n  replica_set_name:\n    default: mongodb-replica\n    description: MongoDB replica set _id used when initiating the set.\n  admin_secret_name:\n    default: admin-user-password\n    description: Kubernetes Secret holding the admin user's password.\n  reporting_secret_name:\n    default: reporting-user-password\n    description: Kubernetes Secret holding the reporting user's password.\n  admin_username:\n    default: admin-user\n    description: Username of the MongoDB admin user.\n  reporting_username:\n    default: reporting-user\n    description: Username of the reporting user.\n  app_database:\n    default: appdb\n    description: Application database holding the reporting collections.\n  reports_collection:\n    default: reports\n    description: Collection backing the reporting dashboards.\n  raw_collection:\n    default: raw\n    description: Collection with ingestion data that must not be exposed.\n  bad_role_name:\n    default: rawRead\n    description: Overly-permissive role initially granted to the reporting user.\n\nprompt: |\n  A 3-member MongoDB replica set is running in the mongodb namespace.\n  Authentication is enabled. Passwords are stored in these Secrets:\n  - {{params.admin_secret_name}}\n  - {{params.reporting_secret_name}}\n\n  Reporting dashboards are failing for {{params.reporting_username}} after a permissions change.\n  Dashboards are built from {{params.app_database}}.{{params.reports_collection}}. {{params.app_database}}.{{params.raw_collection}} contains ingestion data and\n  must not be exposed. Restore the minimum access needed for reporting dashboards.\n\n  Notes:\n  - Do not use operators or CRDs.\n\nnamespace_contract:\n  required_roles: []\n\nmetrics:\n  - time_to_first_mutation\n\npreconditionUnits:\n  - name: mongo_env_ready\n    on_probe_fail: skip\n    probe:\n      # AUTHORITATIVE skip-if-running probe (P32): succeed when the canonical\n      # StatefulSet exists OR any pod is Running, so the destructive namespace\n      # rebuild below is skipped on an inherited cluster even if its pods are\n      # momentarily not Running (mid-restart from a prior stage) -- the\n      # StatefulSet persists across that window. The bare `grep -c Running`\n      # could miss such a cluster and clobber inherited state.\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb get statefulset {{params.cluster_prefix}} >/dev/null 2>&1 || kubectl -n mongodb get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -q Running'\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n    apply:\n      - command: |\n          /bin/sh -c '\n          kubectl delete namespace mongodb --ignore-not-found=true; kubectl wait --for=delete namespace/mongodb --timeout=120s || true\n          '\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl create namespace mongodb\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/custom-roles/resource/secrets.yaml\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/custom-roles/resource/services.yaml\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/custom-roles/resource/statefulset.yaml\"\n        sleep: 5\n      - command: |\n          for i in $(seq 1 120); do\n            ready=$(kubectl -n mongodb get sts {{params.cluster_prefix}} -o jsonpath='{.status.readyReplicas}' 2>/dev/null)\n            if [ \"${ready:-0}\" -ge 3 ]; then\n              exit 0\n            fi\n            sleep 5\n          done\n          exit 1\n        sleep: 2\n      # Pod-Ready != mongod accepting TCP (§1.10): ping-until-ok before rs.initiate.\n      - command: |\n          for i in $(seq 1 30); do\n            kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval 'db.runCommand({ping:1}).ok' 2>/dev/null | grep -q 1 && exit 0\n            sleep 3\n          done\n          exit 1\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: |\n          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval '\n          rs.initiate({_id:\"{{params.replica_set_name}}\",members:[\n            {_id:0,host:\"mongodb-replica-0.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"},\n            {_id:1,host:\"mongodb-replica-1.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"},\n            {_id:2,host:\"mongodb-replica-2.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"}\n          ]})'\n        sleep: 5\n      - command: |\n          for i in $(seq 1 20); do\n            kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval 'db.hello().isWritablePrimary' | grep true && exit 0\n            sleep 3\n          done\n          exit 1\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: |\n          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval '\n          db.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({\n            user: \"{{params.admin_username}}\",\n            pwd: \"admin123password\",\n            roles: [\n              {role: \"clusterAdmin\", db: \"admin\"},\n              {role: \"userAdminAnyDatabase\", db: \"admin\"},\n              {role: \"readWriteAnyDatabase\", db: \"admin\"}\n            ]\n          })'\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: |\n          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet \\\n          \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:admin123password@localhost:27017/admin\" \\\n          --eval 'db.getSiblingDB(\"{{params.app_database}}\").createRole({\n            role: \"{{params.bad_role_name}}\",\n            privileges: [\n              { resource: { db: \"{{params.app_database}}\", collection: \"{{params.raw_collection}}\" }, actions: [\"find\"] }\n            ],\n            roles: []\n          })'\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: |\n          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet \\\n          \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:admin123password@localhost:27017/admin\" \\\n          --eval 'db.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({\n            user: \"{{params.reporting_username}}\",\n            pwd: \"reporting123password\",\n            roles: [{role: \"{{params.bad_role_name}}\", db: \"{{params.app_database}}\"}]\n          })'\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: |\n          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet \\\n          \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:admin123password@localhost:27017/admin\" \\\n          --eval 'db.getSiblingDB(\"{{params.app_database}}\").{{params.reports_collection}}.insertMany([{x:1},{x:2},{x:3}], {writeConcern:{w:1}})'\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: |\n          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet \\\n          \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:admin123password@localhost:27017/admin\" \\\n          --eval 'db.getSiblingDB(\"{{params.app_database}}\").{{params.raw_collection}}.insertMany([{x:10},{x:11}], {writeConcern:{w:1}})'\n        sleep: 2\n    verify:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n\n  - name: admin_user_fixture\n    # Composition self-sufficiency: this case authenticates as the `admin-user`\n    # created at deploy. On an inherited cluster a no-auth/other predecessor may\n    # not have created it, and a live user's password is unrecoverable -> the\n    # oracle's (and the user fixtures') admin auth fails through no agent fault.\n    # Bring our own additively: if admin-user already authenticates, skip; else\n    # ensure the secret and create the user. No restart, no data touched,\n    # idempotent -> never regresses a cluster where admin already works.\n    on_probe_fail: skip\n    probe:\n      - command: |\n          /bin/sh -c '\n          t=\"\"; for cca in /etc/tls/ca.crt /etc/mongo-ca/ca.crt; do kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- ls $cca >/dev/null 2>&1 && { t=\"--tls --tlsAllowInvalidHostnames --tlsAllowInvalidCertificates --tlsCAFile $cca\"; break; }; done\n          pw=$(kubectl -n mongodb get secret admin-user-password -o jsonpath=\"{.data.password}\" 2>/dev/null | base64 -d 2>/dev/null)\n          [ -n \"$pw\" ] || exit 1\n          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet $t \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:$pw@localhost:27017/admin\" --eval \"db.runCommand({ping:1}).ok\" 2>/dev/null | grep -q 1\n          '\n        timeout_sec: 30\n    apply:\n      # Ensure the admin secret (idempotent: create only if missing).\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb get secret admin-user-password >/dev/null 2>&1 || kubectl -n mongodb create secret generic admin-user-password --from-literal=password=admin123password'\"\n        sleep: 1\n      # Ensure the admin-user MongoDB user. On a no-auth inherited cluster this\n      # runs unauthenticated and succeeds; where it already exists it errors and\n      # the `|| true` keeps it a no-op. Never drops or alters existing users/data.\n      - command: |\n          /bin/sh -c '\n          t=\"\"; for cca in /etc/tls/ca.crt /etc/mongo-ca/ca.crt; do kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- ls $cca >/dev/null 2>&1 && { t=\"--tls --tlsAllowInvalidHostnames --tlsAllowInvalidCertificates --tlsCAFile $cca\"; break; }; done\n          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet $t --eval \"db.getSiblingDB(\\\"admin\\\").createUser({user:\\\"{{params.admin_username}}\\\",pwd:\\\"admin123password\\\",roles:[{role:\\\"root\\\",db:\\\"admin\\\"}]})\" 2>/dev/null || true\n          '\n        sleep: 2\n    verify:\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb get secret admin-user-password >/dev/null 2>&1 && echo ok'\"\n        timeout_sec: 15\n\n  # Additive credential+role+seed fixture (composition safety): standalone the\n  # build above creates the reporting-user, its rawRead role, the\n  # reporting-user-password secret, and the reports/raw seed data. Chained on an\n  # INHERITED cluster that build is skipped, so the oracle fails with\n  # \"reporting-user-password not found\". Ensure each artifact additively when\n  # missing, authenticating as the LIVE admin user (a prior rotation respected)\n  # and writing on the current primary. Never drops/alters existing users/data;\n  # standalone the probe finds everything present and skips -> identical behaviour.\n  - name: reporting_user_fixture\n    on_probe_fail: skip\n    probe:\n      - command: |\n          /bin/sh -c 't=\"\"; for cca in /etc/tls/ca.crt /etc/mongo-ca/ca.crt; do kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- ls $cca >/dev/null 2>&1 && { t=\"--tls --tlsAllowInvalidHostnames --tlsAllowInvalidCertificates --tlsCAFile $cca\"; break; }; done; kubectl -n mongodb get secret {{params.reporting_secret_name}} >/dev/null 2>&1 || exit 1; pw=$(kubectl -n mongodb get secret {{params.admin_secret_name}} -o jsonpath=\"{.data.password}\" 2>/dev/null | base64 -d 2>/dev/null); pw=${pw:-admin123password}; P=\"\"; for _pi in $(seq 1 30); do P=$(kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet $t \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:$pw@localhost:27017/admin?directConnection=true\" --eval '\\''rs.hello().primary'\\'' 2>/dev/null | cut -d. -f1); [ -n \"$P\" ] && break; sleep 2; done; P=${P:-mongodb-replica-0}; kubectl -n mongodb exec \"$P\" -- mongosh --quiet $t \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:$pw@localhost:27017/admin\" --eval '\\''db.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").getUser(\"{{params.reporting_username}}\")?quit(0):quit(1)'\\'' >/dev/null 2>&1'\n        timeout_sec: 30\n    apply:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/custom-roles/resource/secrets.yaml\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: |\n          /bin/sh -c 'pw=$(kubectl -n mongodb get secret {{params.admin_secret_name}} -o jsonpath=\"{.data.password}\" 2>/dev/null | base64 -d 2>/dev/null); pw=${pw:-admin123password}; P=\"\"; for _pi in $(seq 1 30); do P=$(kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:$pw@localhost:27017/admin?directConnection=true\" --eval '\\''rs.hello().primary'\\'' 2>/dev/null | cut -d. -f1); [ -n \"$P\" ] && break; sleep 2; done; P=${P:-mongodb-replica-0}; kubectl -n mongodb exec \"$P\" -- mongosh --quiet \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:$pw@localhost:27017/admin\" --eval '\\''var a=db.getSiblingDB(\"{{params.app_database}}\"); if(!a.getRole(\"{{params.bad_role_name}}\")){a.createRole({role:\"{{params.bad_role_name}}\",privileges:[{resource:{db:\"{{params.app_database}}\",collection:\"{{params.raw_collection}}\"},actions:[\"find\"]}],roles:[]});} if(!db.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").getUser(\"{{params.reporting_username}}\")){db.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({user:\"{{params.reporting_username}}\",pwd:\"reporting123password\",roles:[{role:\"{{params.bad_role_name}}\",db:\"{{params.app_database}}\"}]});} if(a.{{params.reports_collection}}.countDocuments({})<3){a.{{params.reports_collection}}.insertMany([{x:1},{x:2},{x:3}],{writeConcern:{w:1}});} if(a.{{params.raw_collection}}.countDocuments({})<2){a.{{params.raw_collection}}.insertMany([{x:10},{x:11}],{writeConcern:{w:1}});}'\\'' 2>&1 || true'\n        sleep: 2\n    verify:\n      - command: |\n          /bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb get secret {{params.reporting_secret_name}} >/dev/null 2>&1; true'\n        timeout_sec: 30\n\noracle:\n  verify:\n    commands:\n      - command: \"python3 cases/mongodb/custom-roles/oracle/oracle.py\"\n        timeout_sec: 150\n","numLines":225,"startLine":1,"totalLines":225}}}
