{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013Fg3i1CArRdzHNnMpBHcXT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand! This is a 3-stage workflow, all using the same `mongodb/custom-roles` case. Each stage has a different `bad_role_name`:\n- Stage 01: `bad_role_name=rawRead` (default)\n- Stage 02: `bad_role_name=overReadRole`\n- Stage 03: `bad_role_name=dbAdminRole` \n\nAll stages run on the same inherited cluster (because the `mongo_env_ready` precondition skips the namespace rebuild if the StatefulSet already exists).\n\nFor Stage 03 specifically, the `reporting_user_fixture` precondition ensures:\n- The role `dbAdminRole` gets created with find privileges on the raw collection in the app database\n- The `reporting-user` is assigned this role in the app database\n- The fixture checks if the role and user already exist before creating them\n\nWriting fixture setup... Since `reporting-user` already exists with the `reportsRead` role from the previous stage, the fixture won't modify it, meaning the user can query `appdb.reports` but not `appdb.raw`. But if Stage 03 is reporting that dashboards are failing, I need to figure out what the broken state actually expects—whether the task requires `reporting-user` to have access to `appdb.raw` instead, or if there's a different misconfiguration at play.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1648,"cache_read_input_tokens":65324,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1648},"output_tokens":32,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"344c96d2-3a99-4ba7-b37e-1a951ea3e6a4","uuid":"c70f3cc7-a79d-4418-8a6c-5929ba0089d3","request_id":"req_011Ccf9LX45p4NTKjTZsB1u3"}
